# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Root .gitignore · catch-all for the whole repo
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# scripts/.gitignore covers Python tooling + .env at that level. This
# file catches things that can land at the repo root or in sibling
# directories (data exports, build artifacts, IDE state, OS junk).
#
# IMPORTANT: never commit a real .env (anywhere). RISKS.md R-003.

# ── Secrets / env ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key

# ── Python ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/
venv/
.venv/

# ── Data exports / client deliverables ───────────────────────────────
# Operator-exported xlsx / csv from Feishu, autowriter, etc. These can
# contain PII and shouldn't accidentally be committed. To version-track
# a sample, place it in data-analysis/ and add a per-file exception.
*.xlsx
*.xls
*.csv
*.tsv
*.parquet
data-exports/
client-data/
exports/

# ── LLM annotation byproducts ────────────────────────────────────────
# annotate_essence_pass.py writes failures here at runtime; reviewable
# locally, not in the repo. The file format is jsonl with raw LLM
# responses (potentially long).
failed_essence_queue.jsonl
failed_*.jsonl

# ── IDE / OS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ── Build / temp ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
build/
dist/
*.log
*.tmp
.cache/
